<FlowDocument xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
              xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
              Foreground="#E0E0E0"
              Background="#1E1F22"
              FontFamily="Segoe UI"
              FontSize="14"
              PagePadding="32,24,32,24">

    <Paragraph FontSize="28" FontWeight="Bold" Foreground="#FFD700" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Create Treasure Event Point
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Foreground="#A0A0A0" FontSize="13" Margin="0,0,0,16">
        Spawns a random bonus item pickup such as Speed, Strength, Constitution, or Reflexes.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,0,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <!-- OVERVIEW -->
    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,4,0,4">
        What Create Treasure Does
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        The <Bold>Create Treasure</Bold> Event Point spawns one of the game’s bonus item pickups.
        These are the special stat-style items associated with <Bold>Speed</Bold>,
        <Bold>Strength</Bold>, <Bold>Constitution</Bold>, and <Bold>Reflexes</Bold>.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        This Event Point is simple compared with many mission logic Event Points. It does not create
        an NPC, does not require complex linking, and does not contain many type-specific fields.
        Its purpose is to place a bonus pickup into the mission.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_create_treasure_overview.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,8,0,8">
        <Border Background="#2A2F3A" BorderBrush="#4A5A7A" BorderThickness="1"
                CornerRadius="4" Padding="12">
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Foreground="#AFC8FF">
                <Run FontWeight="Bold">Simple summary:</Run>
                <Run>
                    Create Treasure places a bonus pickup at the Event Point location. The creator chooses where it appears,
                    when it appears, and the points value. The exact bonus item type is chosen randomly by the game.
                </Run>
            </TextBlock>
        </Border>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <!-- ADDING -->
    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Adding a Create Treasure Event Point
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        To add a treasure pickup, click <Bold>Add</Bold> in the Event Points panel, select
        <Bold>Create Treasure</Bold> from the Event Point type list, and click <Bold>OK</Bold>.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        The <Bold>Edit EventPoint</Bold> window opens with the normal common properties, trigger
        settings, and the Create Treasure-specific points field.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_create_treasure_add_type.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <!-- COMMON PROPERTIES -->
    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,12,0,4">
        Common Properties
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        Create Treasure uses the standard Event Point common properties. These include the automatic
        index number, automatic Event Point type, letter group, colour, position, trigger settings,
        and listening mode.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        The most important common property for this Event Point is the <Bold>position</Bold>, because
        that controls where the bonus item appears in the mission.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_create_treasure_common_properties.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="18" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#9FE3A6" Margin="0,10,0,4">
        Position
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        Use <Bold>Select Position on Map</Bold> to place the treasure pickup visually in the
        viewport. The pickup spawns at the Event Point location when the Event Point triggers.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        Place treasure in a location that makes sense for the mission. For example, it might be used
        as a reward at the end of a difficult route, behind a search objective, inside a dangerous
        area, or near the completion point of an optional challenge.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_create_treasure_position.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <!-- RANDOM TYPE -->
    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Bonus Item Type Is Random
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        There is no field for choosing exactly which bonus item will appear. The Event Point can
        spawn one of the bonus item types, but the exact type is decided by the game at random.
    </Paragraph>

    <List MarkerStyle="Disc" Margin="16,2,0,0">
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Speed</Bold>.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Strength</Bold>.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Constitution</Bold>.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Reflexes</Bold>.</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>

    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        The mission creator cannot force this Event Point to specifically spawn Speed, Strength,
        Constitution, or Reflexes. The creator controls the Event Point position, trigger behaviour,
        and points value, but not the exact bonus category.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,8,0,8">
        <Border Background="#4A2424" BorderBrush="#C45A5A" BorderThickness="2"
                CornerRadius="4" Padding="14">
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Foreground="#FFD0D0" FontSize="15">
                <Run FontWeight="Bold">Critical limitation:</Run>
                <Run>
                    You cannot select the exact bonus item type. Create Treasure chooses randomly between the bonus item types.
                    Do not build mission logic that depends on this Event Point spawning one specific bonus category.
                </Run>
            </TextBlock>
        </Border>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <!-- SPECIFIC PROPERTY -->
    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Create Treasure Properties
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        Create Treasure has only one type-specific property: <Bold>Points</Bold>.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_create_treasure_properties.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="18" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#9FE3A6" Margin="0,10,0,4">
        Points
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        The <Bold>Points</Bold> value is associated with the spawned treasure item. Typical values
        are in the range of <Bold>5–50 points</Bold>.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        The editor may provide quick value buttons or quick values for common point amounts. Use
        these as convenience shortcuts when you want to assign a standard reward value quickly.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        Because the exact bonus item type is random, the Points value is the main type-specific
        control available to the mission creator.
    </Paragraph>

    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <!-- TRIGGER SETTINGS -->
    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Trigger Settings
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        Like most Event Points, Create Treasure can be active from the start of the mission or placed
        behind another trigger.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontSize="18" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#9FE3A6" Margin="0,10,0,4">
        Spawn Immediately
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        If the treasure should appear as soon as the mission starts, use:
    </Paragraph>

    <List MarkerStyle="Disc" Margin="16,2,0,0">
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Triggered By:</Bold> None / Game Starts.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Listening Mode:</Bold> Active.</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>

    <Paragraph FontSize="18" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#9FE3A6" Margin="0,10,0,4">
        Spawn After a Condition
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        If the treasure should act as a reward, place it behind a trigger. For example, it could
        appear after:
    </Paragraph>

    <List MarkerStyle="Disc" Margin="16,2,0,0">
        <ListItem><Paragraph>An NPC is arrested or killed.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>A counter reaches a required value.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>A conversation finishes.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>The player enters a specific area.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>A sub-objective or optional task is completed.</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>

    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        Use whichever trigger best matches the mission condition that should make the bonus item
        appear.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_create_treasure_trigger_settings.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <!-- EXAMPLES -->
    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Practical Examples
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Reward for Exploring</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">
        Place a treasure pickup at the end of an alley, rooftop route, hidden area, or optional
        exploration path. Use None / Game Starts if it should always be available.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Reward for a Sub-Mission</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">
        Place Create Treasure behind a dependency or counter trigger so it appears only after a
        side task is completed.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Reward After Arresting a Target</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">
        Use a trigger such as Person Arrested if the treasure should spawn after the player arrests a
        specific NPC. In that case, make sure the trigger’s target/reference points to the correct
        NPC Event Point.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Small Bonus Pickup</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">
        Use a low value such as 5 or 10 points for minor rewards.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Major Optional Reward</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="24,0,0,0">
        Use a higher value such as 25 or 50 points for a more significant optional challenge.
    </Paragraph>

    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <!-- WORKFLOW -->
    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,12,0,4">
        Basic Create Treasure Workflow
    </Paragraph>
    <List MarkerStyle="Decimal" Margin="16,2,0,0">
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Click <Bold>Add</Bold> in the Event Points panel.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Select <Bold>Create Treasure</Bold> and click <Bold>OK</Bold>.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Choose a letter group and colour that fits your mission organisation.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Use <Bold>Select Position on Map</Bold> to place the treasure pickup location.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Set the <Bold>Points</Bold> value, usually somewhere around <Bold>5–50</Bold>.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Choose the trigger that controls when the treasure appears.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Use <Bold>None / Game Starts</Bold> and <Bold>Active</Bold> if it should appear immediately.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Use a dependency, counter, radius, person, or other trigger if it should appear as a reward.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Click <Bold>OK</Bold>, save the mission, and test it in game.</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,8,0,8">
        <Border Background="#2A3A2A" BorderBrush="#4A7A4A" BorderThickness="1"
                CornerRadius="4" Padding="12">
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Foreground="#A0E0A0">
                <Run FontWeight="Bold">Final note:</Run>
                <Run>
                    Create Treasure is simple, but do not over-specify it in mission logic.
                    You can control where and when it appears, and how many points it is worth.
                    You cannot control whether it becomes Speed, Strength, Constitution, or Reflexes.
                </Run>
            </TextBlock>
        </Border>
    </BlockUIContainer>

</FlowDocument>